  • Chinese presentation and final will not be accepted and get no score!

Course Description

  • Industrial Organization is study of firms and industries.
    • Using theory of the firm to examine structure of and boundaries between firms and markets
    • markets that deviate from the basic competitive model
      • transaction costs, limited information, barriers to entry
  • Prominent topics will include oligopoly, cartel behavior, anti-competitive practices, price discrimination, and government regulation.

Course Schedule

  • The material of the textbook is summarized below.
    • Part1: Introduction and Theory
    • Part2: Market Structure
    • Part3: Business Practices: Strategies & Conduct
    • Part4: Information, Advertising, and Disclosure
    • Part5: Dynamic Models and Market Clearing
    • Part6: Government Policies and Their Effects
  • We will try to cover parts I, II and III. And then, depends on time and your interest, I will try to cover more chapters.
